Several lawyers were illegally searched when attending the trial of Xuelixingxing pyramid scheme case. The bailiff refused to show the legal basis and expelled the lawyers. The lawyer asked the bailiff to provide the police number and was sprayed with pepper spray in the face by the bailiff

name: 李老师不是你老师

Recently, a video circulated online showed that a netizen was asked by the police to check his phone to see if he had taken any photos while watching the police enforce the law in a public place, and was asked not to take any photos or videos.
The man insisted that he had the right to take photos and did not hinder their enforcement or break the law.
At 1 minute and 12 seconds in the video, another police officer threatened: We don’t want you to get involved in the matter. If you post (the video), we will hold you legally responsible.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On December 24, Tustin Burgers had raw meat, and the store only refunded 30 yuan.
A netizen posted a video saying that he ate raw meat patties at the well-known hamburger chain Tustin. The video showed that the patties were not cooked at all and the meat did not change color. After reporting it to the store, only 30.9 yuan was refunded, and no additional compensation was given.
The store said that it was an employee's operating error and the chicken steak was not fried thoroughly.
Raw chicken contains parasites and relatively more bacteria, which may cause diarrhea and parasitic infections.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Recently, a netizen reported on Xiaohongshu that Peng Zhubin, the former dean of Hunan University, leaked the national postgraduate entrance examination questions. The reporter said: Peng Zhubin revealed the test questions of Volume A and B of Hunan University's self-proposed course "Basics of Journalism and Communication" to multiple candidates before the exam, helping them cheat. Cheating in the postgraduate entrance examination is now a criminal offense, and organizing cheating is punishable by a prison sentence of less than 3 years. Currently, the post was first banned from commenting by Xiaohongshu, and then deleted by Xiaohongshu.

December 26th Weibo Hot Search: 21-year-old blind girl marries 58-year-old man, sparking heated discussion
Recently, a man in Chongqing updated videos every day, recording "What is it like to be a father at the age of 58?" Multiple videos showed that the 58-year-old man married a 21-year-old girl and claimed to have been abused online. The man said that his wife was a disabled person, blind, and suffered from depression. The man had never been married before, and this was his first marriage.

December 25th: Official rumor: The prevalence of depression among Chinese adolescents is 15% is a rumor. Experts: The authoritative survey results are about 2%, but netizens questioned it.

According to the results of the authoritative agency survey, the prevalence of depression among adolescents in my country is actually only about 2%.
Comment area netizens: If it is not diagnosed, it does not exist.

On December 25, a blogger published an article accusing CCTV of stealing the photos he took.
The blogger was invited to participate in the 53rd anniversary of China-US Ping Pong Diplomacy. He took a camera and took two photos and posted them on social media. The next day, he found that CCTV Sports had stolen the photos and removed the watermarks through PS. Later, a number of local media and Sina also followed CCTV in reposting the photos.
The blogger questioned CCTV's operation, which violated the principles of copyright and the authenticity of news photos.
